## Enterprise Components (Commercial License)

The following components require a commercial license for use:

- **Enterprise Client** (`packages/client/`)
  - Advanced UI/UX components
  - Dashboard builder
  - Real-time collaboration
  - White-label customization

- **Enterprise Authentication** (`packages/auth/`)
  - SSO/SAML integration
  - Multi-factor authentication
  - Advanced RBAC
  - Audit logging
  - Compliance features

- **Advanced Features**
  - AntV MCP integration
  - Database/warehouse connectors
  - Predictive analytics
  - Anomaly detection
  - Enterprise governance

### Commercial License Terms

For commercial use of enterprise components, please contact:

**BigStack Analytics**
- Email: licensing@bigstack-analytics.com
- Website: https://bigstack-analytics.com
- Phone: [Contact Information]

Commercial licenses include:
- ✅ Production use rights
- ✅ Technical support
- ✅ Service level agreements
- ✅ Professional services
- ✅ Custom development
- ✅ White-label licensing

## Evaluation License

Enterprise components may be used for evaluation purposes for up to 30 days without a commercial license. After the evaluation period, a commercial license is required for continued use.

## Contributing

Contributions to open source components are welcome under the MIT License. Contributors to enterprise components must sign a Contributor License Agreement (CLA).

## Questions?

For licensing questions, please contact licensing@bigstack-analytics.com